# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Python
__pycache__/

# Node (if any tooling is added later)
node_modules/

# Smart Web Search cache (per-project, generated at runtime)
.smart-search-cache/

# Antigravity CLI (agy) per-project tracking — runtime state, created when agy
# touches the project. Symlinks into ~/.gemini/config/projects/<UUID>.json.
.antigravitycli/

# Commit-gate review attestation (per-project runtime state). Written by the
# /commit skill's runner (commit-gate/commit-gate-runner.sh) and verified by the
# commit-gate PreToolUse hook. Never committed — it binds to the local tree SHA.
.commit-gate/

# Evolve Loop runtime state (generated per-project, not part of the plugin)
# Ignore every direct child of .evolve/ ...
# v8.21.0+: per-cycle git worktrees live at .evolve/worktrees/cycle-N — also
# implicitly ignored by this rule. Worktrees are created by run-cycle.sh
# and removed via its EXIT trap; they should never appear in commits.
.evolve/*
**/.evolve/
# ... except the agent permission profiles, which ship with the plugin and are
# required by scripts/subagent-run.sh for least-privilege subagent invocation.
!.evolve/profiles/
.evolve/profiles/*
!.evolve/profiles/*.json
!.evolve/profiles/*.md
# ... and except the directory marker for failure-lessons. Generated lesson
# YAMLs (inst-L*.yaml) are per-project runtime state and remain ignored, but
# the .keep marker ships so the directory exists in fresh installs.
!.evolve/instincts/
.evolve/instincts/*
!.evolve/instincts/lessons/
.evolve/instincts/lessons/*
!.evolve/instincts/lessons/.keep
# ... and except the inbox API directory. Operator-injected task files in the root
# of inbox/ are tracked; processed/ and rejected/ are runtime subdirs (gitignored).
!.evolve/inbox/
.evolve/inbox/processed/
.evolve/inbox/rejected/
# ... and except the subagent-skills plugin directory. Loaded by Builder/Auditor
# subagents via --plugin-dir to make review skills (code-review-simplify,
# security-review-scored) resolvable under --setting-sources project. Manifest
# is tracked; skills/ entries are symlinks to .agents/skills/ (also tracked).
!.evolve/plugin/
!.evolve/plugin/.claude-plugin/
!.evolve/plugin/.claude-plugin/plugin.json
!.evolve/plugin/skills/
!.evolve/plugin/skills/*
# ... and except the Layer 1 (ADR-0012) commit-prefix manifest. Defines what
# commit prefixes (docs:, feat(guards):, etc.) require which diff paths.
# Operator-extensible but ships with sensible defaults; must be tracked so the
# scripts/guards/commit-prefix-gate.sh hook applies consistently across clones.
!.evolve/commit-prefix-scope.json
# ... and except user-defined phase specs. Operators drop a phase.json under
# .evolve/phases/<name>/phase.json to extend the pipeline declaratively.
# Analogous to .evolve/profiles/ — must be tracked so new phases ship with the
# project and survive clone. (recoverBuildLeak already skips .evolve/ paths, so
# tracking these files does not re-introduce the cycle-176 incident.)
!.evolve/phases/
.evolve/phases/*
!.evolve/phases/*/
.evolve/phases/*/*
!.evolve/phases/*/phase.json
# NOTE (issue-#11 / cycle-176): a self-evolve cycle (ee77067) un-ignored .evolve/
# (`!.evolve/` + `!.evolve/evals/`) to "track evals". That broke a LOAD-BEARING
# invariant — recoverBuildLeak (go/internal/core/orchestrator.go) and the audit
# assume .evolve/ is fully gitignored; un-ignoring it exposed ~300 eval files to
# `git status`, which the leak-recovery then tried to relocate/`git add` and
# aborted the cycle. Reverted to keep .evolve/ runtime state ignored. Versioning
# eval definitions, if desired, must be a deliberate redesign that also updates the
# recovery/audit machinery — not a blanket un-ignore.
.claude/evolve/
.claude/worktrees/
.clone/
.ruff_cache/
*.pyc

# Cycle 65 incident: prevent stderr-redirected warnings from being committed.
# role-context-builder.sh anchor-validation can emit a stderr WARN that
# Orchestrator captures as `warn.txt` at repo root. ship.sh `git add -A`
# would then sweep it into the cycle commit (causes audit-bound tree-SHA
# drift; see docs/incidents/cycle-65-warn-txt.md if/when authored).
/warn.txt
*.warn
parity-audit-report.md

# Phase-report runtime artifacts. Agents write these to their cwd (a per-cycle
# worktree = a checkout of this repo), and the builder's `git add -A` + worktree
# commit will sweep them into the repo root if they aren't ignored — that is how
# a stale `build-report.md` (Cycle 65, 27bee92) ended up tracked and got
# relocated into cycle-145 by artifactReady's worktree search (audit FAIL on a
# wrong challenge token). These belong only under .evolve/runs/cycle-N/.
build-report.md
scout-report.md
audit-report.md
triage-report.md
test-report.md
build-plan.md
*-reflection.yaml

# Go coverage artifacts (`go test -coverprofile`). Never commit: left untracked
# they get swept into cycle commits by `git add -A` and drift the committed tree
# from the audit-bound tree (INTEGRITY_TREE_DRIFT, cycle-152).
cover.out
coverage.out
*.coverprofile
